########## This file contains information on the input prescription for Recipe == 3: "getPDF"
########## Mandatory inputs:
Recipe                      3                       # "getHist"
colrby                      KE-diss-rate            # [common options are: KE-diss-rate,Lambda2,T-diss-rate,p,u,v,w,vort_x,vort_y,vort_z,vort-mag,stab-index]
datRng                      -8.0,5.0                # data range for which the histogram is calculated
########## Optional inputs:
histLg                      1                       # Switch to turn on histogram plotting on log10 scale; NOTE: If this is set to 1, recheck the 'datRng' input above to ensure the data range in specified for log scale and not linear scale of dataset
numBins                     250                     # The number of bins to sort the histogram data into
#extSS                       1                       # Extract subset/subvolume from DNS domain
### ONLY IF 'extSS' is set to 1
#domXYZ                      120,42,24               # The Simulation Box size
#x                           40,80                   # The x1-x2 Extent for the plane/volume
#y                           15,42                   # The y1-y2 Extent for the plane/volume
#z                           0,18                    # The z1-z2 Extent for the plane/volume
#N                           5040,1470,1680          # The number of mesh points in X, Y, and Z for the simulation Domain
#subSamp                     1,1,1                   # The subsampling rate applied to the data
